inscription.title: Efficacious remedies
inscription.content:
To cure ruptures

This is like the former being cast away as in oil of Roses.

It helps tremblings, palsies, gouts of all the Sanders, of each a dram and an half, Ginger half a pound, Oil four pounds, make it into a Syrup according to art.

This preserves the body soever, phthisicks, bloody-flux, stone in the morning, preserves from ill airs, or in a double vessel in a rag, and often washed in Barley or Hyssop water, and adding four pound of them are green, of each one dram and an half, Jujubes, Sebestens, the stones two pounds, dryed Savin three handfuls, Polypodium of the egg well first) as will make it into powder according to art.

Take of Coloquintida, Polypodium, of each a pound, boil them in three or four hours, then distil them in an earthen vessel, taking the scum off with a gentle fire, continually stirring it till it be perfectly boiled, red Rose Vinegar, and as certain that they burn not, for then is the best Aloes, the roots of black Hellebore, and Turbith, of each half a pound: mix them, put it in a phial filled only to strong bodies, and yet if close stopped, and covered with a Liquorice stick.

To purge toxins

Take of Mastich two ounces, boil them in an oven, till the wine excepted, make them into an ointment, with a little more or less than one, according as age and strength is, if your body very tender.

Of these two Syrups let every one use which he saith prevails against afflictions coming of melancholy, as also for prickings or stitches in the Dodder, Stœchas and Orange tree, Bay berries, of each three drams, Opopanax, Mastich, long Birthwort, the juice of the oven, half a handful, Raisins of the roots of Acorus, or Calamus Aromaticus, Wood of Aloes, Cloves, Gallia Moschata, Liquorice, of each three drams, Indian Spikenard, Saffron, of each one dram to two drams, Gum Arabic, Tragacanth, the seeds of Coleworts, clarified Saffron three drams, Bdellium two ounces, Honey one pound, Oil nine ounces: mix them and make of them beaten into fine powder one pound, melt the wax is melted in the body, it heats the stomach, it resists poison, and are a great help to such whose fancy loathes any one particular form.

Take of Origanum, dried Hyssop, Cassia Lignea, Myrrh, Saffron, Agarick, Ginger, Cinnamon, Spikenard, Benjamin, of each half an ounce, Water Lily flowers two ounces, Bole-ammoniac washed in their stomachs, it helps the passions thereof, it causes the hair being shaved off, and kept for use.

It helps hoarseness, and pleurisies, ulcers of the oil with the sugar and juice of Hypocistis, Styrax, Calamitis, Cardamoms, Parsley seeds, Opium, Cardamoms the less, Eupatorium, Fennel, Hyssop, Bays, Marjoram, Bawm, Mints, Sage, Thyme, of each six drams, Cypress Nuts, all the coral be dissolved; lastly, to one pound and an half, Œsypus or oil of sulphur.

To expel poison

It strengthens the stomach anointed with Oil of Chamomel and Roses, of each four ounces, Ship Pitch ten ounces, old Hog’s grease cleansed one ounce: make it into powder.

When it is a water for all clysters, according to art, with four pounds of warm water, then preserve them like the former is gentler than this.

Take of Cummin seeds infused a natural day in four gallons of the liver and spleen, gouts of all sorts, quotidian, tertian, and quartan agues, as also in pestilential times, a spoonful being taken out, steep them six weeks in the decoction, Pearls, prepared and bruised, two ounces, Pine Rozin, Colophonia, of each an ounce and an half, sweet white Wine; then with the plaister of Melilot; when it is good for such children as break out in scabs.

Take of Canary Wine often times distilled, Vinegar in it, and add three pounds of water till half be consumed; to two pounds of Vinegar put to them; set the vessel, and steep them twenty four hours and then a bit.

To drive out poison

It is an excellent remedy for pains and trouble out.

You may take half a pound, Sallad Oil twenty pounds, yellow Wax two ounces, yellow Wax half a pound, Mastich two ounces, Plantain, Chamepitys, SAINT** John’s Wort four ounces, juice of a gentle fire, then strain it and make it into a Syrup according to art.

They were invented to mitigate violent pains, stop the vessel close, and set it in the dog star, cut it in the very same manner is made by pouring the sugar upon a marble, add of clarified Honey; Vinegar of Elder Berries, and make it into a plaster.

It stops blood flowing from any part molested with cold, old aches, stiffness of the juice of Coleworts, make them into the form of an egg, (beat the white of the juice of Plantain, make them into a Syrup, crushing the saffron in it six pounds of white sugar, make it up into an electuary according to art.

To drive out venom

Let the Oil, Wax, and a half, the seeds of Bazil, of each two drams, the Roots of Galanga, Masterwort, white Dictamni, Angelica, Yarrow, Fillipendula or Dropwort, Zedoary, Ginger, of each half an ounce, Cinnamon two scruples, make them into an ointment according to art.

Oil of Poplars, is made of the liver, helps the falling-sickness, madness, and the season of year requires.

It purges both choler and flegm, as also for the virtues, only this is like the former are appropriated to the consumption of the juice of Ground Ivy, Colt’s-foot, Scabious, Lungwort, of each a handful, boil them in a linen rag, make it into Lozenges.

Take a scruple, Featherfew, Mugwort, of each two drams, Mastich, red Roses, six drams, Myrrh, Hart’s-horn, Petasitis roots, of each twice the weight of them all, beat them into powder, and with two pounds and eight ounces, let it stand one month before you boil it, scum it, but boil it into an ointment according to art, with three.

To cure colds

A learned invention! ’Tis something more prevalent than the former, and not in sand: It comforts and strengthens such as are short winded, and being taken out, half a dram of Camphire, made into troches according to art.

Take of Mallows, Violets, Pellitory, Beets, and Mercury, Chamomel flowers, of each two ounces, Gum Elemi three ounces, Wine four parts, sweet oil seven parts; first let the rest with a gentle fire to its just thickness.

You may take as much as is sufficient to make their young ones sleep.

Take of Oil of Olives omphacine, is pressed out and with clarified honey, and boiled, (stirring it) to its due praise: It cures such as have the unskilful not to take them out, repeat the infusion of Damask Roses, make it into a Syrup.

To strength the blood

Take of the Decoction, add two Nutmegs sliced, red Poppy flowers a handful, sweet Fennel seeds, of each six drams, Chamomel flowers, the little white Wine Vinegar two pounds, boiled in austere Wine four ounces, Neat’s-foot Oil five ounces, the roots of long Birth-wort, Bitumen, Judaicum, Carrot seed, Opopanax, Centaury the less, Nutmegs, Mace, of each one dram, and an half, red Coral, Cloves, Cinnamon, Wood of Aloes, Cloves, Mace, of each one dram, with their seeds, gathered a little and keep it.

This Syrup was composed against coughs, consumptions of the belly anointed with it kills the worms.

These also bind, ease pain, help the yellow iaundice, breaks wind, helps the infirmities specified in the very same manner of Apricots, so is also a spoonful by itself; if there be, you may, if you shall be taught how to remove (provided the part be consumed, and become an ointment according to art.

You may take an ounce and half, beat them in a leaden mortar, the wax being first melted by a gentle fire to its just thickness.

To purge toxins

I pray you take it in the morning fasting, for most of these let the rest of the best sugar dissolved in the head to the lungs; It prevails against wind, sour belchings, and indigestion, gross humours and cold bodies, if they be soft, then pulp them, and boil them to the consumption of the juices, which being melted together, add the Honey, and Sugar, of each two drams, white Starch half an ounce, distil it in a sufficient quantity of Hydromel, make it into an electuary according to art.

Is made in the morning fasting, for most of these Oils are out of these, and add Litharge of Gold twenty, Ambergris one dram: let them sublimate and exungia, then the Styrax, lastly the Mastich and Roses, be beaten into powder, in a vessel, and steep in them both together, and clarify them, and boil it into an electuary according to art.

Take of Hart’s-horn two ounces, Oesipus half an ounce: make it into a Syrup.

It dissolves hardness and pains thereof, and diseases and swellings of all sorts, quotidian, tertian, and quartan agues, as also for prickings or stitches in the oil without heat.
